\[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="2540"\]![ This ain’t your grandpa’s Doomday. Credit DC Comics ](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/7788ca7c-5a05-4a87-9441-574cf6848138/DC+Preview+Superman+%2323.jpg?format=original) This ain’t your grandpa’s Doomday. Credit DC Comics \[/caption\]

Superman’s latest adventure has him face to face-to-face with one of his most dangerous foes yet! Written by Joshua Williamson, with stunning artwork by Dan Mora, Alejandro Sánchez, and Ariana Maher, **_Enemy of My Enemy_** is a pivotal chapter in the ongoing **_Many Deaths of Doomsda_**_y_ arc. This issue not only deepens the stakes of the story but also lays the groundwork for major developments in Superman’s journey this summer. Check it out when **_Superman #23_** hits shelves on February 26th!

* * *

## Official Preview for SUperman #23

\[caption id="" align="alignnone" width="1988"\]![ Superman #23 Cover A by Dan Mora ](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/2cddb214-ae62-469b-a4b3-491fe2cc47cc/SM23_Cvr_Main_Dan+Mora.jpg?format=original) Superman #23 Cover A by Dan Mora \[/caption\]

## Synopsis:

As the Man of Steel battles for the life of his deadliest adversary Doomsday, Superwoman travels across time and space to unlock the secrets of the Time Trapper!

What life-shattering secrets lurk at the end of time? What clues can Lois Lane find to save the future? And can these answers be uncovered in time to halt Time Trapper’s evolution into God-Mode?

**_Variant Covers by Dan Panosian, Guillem March, Nathan Szerdy, Dave Johnson, and Kaare Andrews (Batman: Hush variant)_**

